# ÖTILLÖ Utö — Training Schedule (May 11 – June 6)

## Principles
- **Taper the last week** — don't arrive tired
- **Prioritize muscular transition under fatigue** — the core skill of swimrun, trained via pool strength intervals and outdoor gym run breaks
- **Address the cramping** — longer sessions with active electrolyte intake every 30–40 min
- **Arms-only swim training** — all pool sessions use paddles + pull buoy to mimic race conditions
- **2 real wetsuit brick sessions** — one in Week 2, one in Week 3, to practice open water swim→run transition

---

## Session Formats

### 🏊 Pool Strength Intervals
Instead of a single continuous swim, break the session into segments with poolside bodyweight exercises between each. This trains muscular transition (the shock of standing up after swimming) and targets cramping.
- Example exercises: squats, lunges, calf raises, jump squats
- Keep rest short — the point is to move while fatigued

### 🏃 Outdoor Gym Run Breaks
Break longer runs at outdoor gym stations for upper body work. Pull-ups and rows are especially race-relevant since your arms do all the swim work. Arriving at a gym stop with tired legs mimics reaching a swim leg during the race.
- Example exercises: pull-ups, ring rows, dead hangs, dips
- 1–2 stops per run, ~5–10 min each

### 🌊 Wetsuit Brick (Outdoor)
Full race simulation: open water swim in wetsuit → run directly after without changing. Practice pulling off wetsuit top while moving, paddles on, pull buoy clipped. Do these on a lake or sea swim spot.

